chapter.article:
1. The Parties to this Agreement grant each other the concessions specified in Protocol 2 in accordance with the provisions of this Chapter and those laid down in this Protocol. 


2. Taking account of: 
-the role of agriculture in their economies; 
-the development of trade in agricultural products between the Parties; 
-the particular sensitivity of the agricultural products; 
-the rules of their agricultural policies; 


-the consequences of the multilateral trade negotiations under the General Agreement on Tariffs and Trade and of the World Trade Organization, the Parties shall examine the possibilities of granting each other further concessions.
